	<h3><i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i> Criteria for winning</h3>
	<p>The CoderDojo iDEA competition is for individuals residing in Ireland or the United Kingdom only and under the age of 17 as of 10th December 2017.</p>
	<p>Winners will be contacted via the email address used to sign-up to <a href="https://idea.org.uk/invite/BO2EH" target="_blank">iDEA.org.uk</a>.</p>
	<p>There will only be 1 winner per category. If there is more than 1 winner in the category, then the winner will be chosen via random.org.uk.</p>
	<p>If the winner is unable to attend on the day of the ceremony, their award will be posted to them either at home or at school.</p>
	<p>An individual can receive one award in total.</p>

	<p><strong>Award categories are:</strong></p>
		<ul>
			<li>Most Citizen Badge points awarded.</li>
			<li>Most Worker Badge points awarded.</li>
			<li>Most Maker Badge points awarded.</li>
			<li>Most Entrepreneur Badge points awarded.</li>
			<li>Most points awarded across all categories including Gamer.</li>
			<li>Most Badge points awarded in a day.</li>
			<li>Most Badge points awarded during the competition.</li>
			<li>Best New Badge idea for iDEA.</li>
			<li>Most Influential individual (using the iDEA Influencer badge, the person who can create the highest number of referrals from 1st March to 10th December, 2017).</li>
			<li>Most Influential individual (using the iDEA Influencer badge, the person who can create the highest number of referrals in any given week from 1st March to 10th December, 2017).</li>
		</ul>

	<p>For any questions or inquries about the criteria or categories, please email us at ideacompetition@coderdojo.london.</p>

